WEBVTT

00:15:27.465 --> 00:15:31.734
Fewer than two percent of the clients
that we provided bail assistance for

00:15:31.758 --> 00:15:34.280
ever got convicted of a crime at all.

00:15:34.304 --> 00:15:37.727
So there were people that wound up
being convicted of violations,

00:15:37.751 --> 00:15:39.705
which are less than criminal convictions,

00:15:39.729 --> 00:15:42.207
which will have far fewer
consequences in the future.

00:15:42.231 --> 00:15:44.557
It was a staggering finding.

00:15:44.581 --> 00:15:46.344
CA: So this is an amazing difference,

00:15:46.368 --> 00:15:48.563
just the difference
between paying bail or not.

00:15:48.587 --> 00:15:53.213
In one instance, 90 percent of people
who are stuck in jail plead guilty,

00:15:53.237 --> 00:15:56.732
and in the other instance, only two
percent of them end up --

00:15:56.756 --> 00:15:59.057
RS: With a criminal conviction
and going to jail.

